{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\deff0\deftab720\deflang2057{\fonttbl{\f0\fswiss Arial;}{\f1\fswiss \fcharset0 Arial;}}{\colortbl\red0\green0\blue0;\red0\green128\blue0;\red0\green0\blue0;\red0\green0\blue255;}\pard \plain \plain\f0\fs20\cf1 \protect <NS 1>\plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs24\cf3\b Using the Command Line Application\plain\f0\fs20\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2  \plain\f0\fs20\cf1 \protect </NS 1>\plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 A command line tool, \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\i CHInst\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 , comes bundled with \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\i Component Help Installer\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 . It integrates or de-integrate\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 s\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\i OpenHelp\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  compatible help files with \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\i Delphi\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  v3\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  to v7\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 . The purpose of this tool is to enable component help files to be installed in \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\i Delphi\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  from batch files, installers etc.
\par \plain\f0\fs12\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\b Modes of operation\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\i CHInst\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  has three modes of operation:
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \pard \fi-400 \li400 \tx400 \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 1)\tab \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 5>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 installing help files\plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 5>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  into the \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\i Delphi\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  IDE.
\par 2)\tab \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 4>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 uninstalling help files\plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 4>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  registered by the GUI application\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 or \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\i CHInst\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 .
\par 3)\tab \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 7>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 displaying help information\plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 7>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  on the console.
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \pard \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 To simplify installation and uninstallation on different versions of \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\i Delphi\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 , \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\i CHInst\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  supports the use of \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 6>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 file path macros\plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 6>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 .
\par \plain\f0\fs12\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\b Return codes\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 If \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\i CHInst\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  successfully completes an installation / uninstallation then the program returns 0 to the operating system or calling program. If an error is encountered a positive number is returned.
\par \plain\f0\fs12\cf2 
