{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\deff0\deftab720\deflang2057{\fonttbl{\f0\fswiss Arial;}{\f1\fswiss \fcharset0 Arial;}{\f2\fnil \fcharset0 Courier New;}}{\colortbl\red0\green0\blue0;\red0\green128\blue0;\red0\green0\blue0;\red0\green0\blue255;}\pard \plain \plain\f0\fs20\cf1 \protect <NS 1>\plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs24\cf3\b Installing Help Files Using The Command Line\plain\f0\fs20\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2  \plain\f0\fs20\cf1 \protect </NS 1>\plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 This topic describes how to install help files using the \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\i CHInst \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 command line tool.
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\i CHInst\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  can:
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \pard \fi-400 \li400 \tx400 \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 a)\tab copy help files to the required installation folder
\par b)\tab register the help file with Windows
\par c)\tab record a description of the file that appears in help find dialogs
\par d)\tab work with any version of Delphi from v3 onwards
\par \pard \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 The command to issue to install a help file \plain\f1\fs18\cf2 (all on one line) \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 is:
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \pard \li400 \plain\f2\fs18\cf1 \protect <KP 4>\plain\f2\fs18\cf2 CHInst [-i] \plain\f2\fs18\cf2\i source_help_file\plain\f2\fs18\cf1\i \protect </KP 4>\plain\f2\fs18\cf2 
\par \pard \li800 \plain\f2\fs18\cf1 \protect <KP 6>\plain\f2\fs18\cf2 [-c \plain\f2\fs18\cf2\i dest_help_file\plain\f2\fs18\cf2 ]\plain\f2\fs18\cf1 \protect </KP 6>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f2\fs18\cf1 \protect <KP 7>\plain\f2\fs18\cf2 [-d \plain\f2\fs18\cf2\i description\plain\f2\fs18\cf2 ] [-v\plain\f2\fs18\cf2\i X\plain\f2\fs18\cf2 ] [-q]\plain\f2\fs18\cf1 \protect </KP 7>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par \pard \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 The switches and parameters are described below.
\par \plain\f0\fs12\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\b the -i switch\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 This switch is optional. It tells \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\i CHInst\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  to perform an installation rather than an uninstallation. Leaving the switch out has the same effect as including it. 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 If provided the -i switch must be the first item on the command line. \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\i source_help_file\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  specifies the name of the help file to be installed. This parameter is compulsory and must follow the -i switch where provided, or be the first parameter if the -i switch is omitted.
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 The \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\i source_help_file\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  path can include a \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 5>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 file path macro\plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 5>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 .
\par \plain\f0\fs12\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\b the -c switch
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 If the -c switch is used then \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\i source_help_file\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  is copied to \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\i dest_help_file\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  and \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\i dest_help_file\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  is registered with the Delphi IDE. If the -c switch is not used then the help file given by \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\i source_help_file\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  is registered with Delphi and integrated into the IDE.
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 The \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\i dest_help_file\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  path can include a file path macro.
\par \plain\f0\fs12\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\b the -d switch\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 This switch registers the following parameter as a \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\i description\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  of the help file with the Delphi IDE. The \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\i description\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  appears in topic list dialogs. (The \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\i description\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  parameter must be enclosed in "" quotes if it contains spaces).
\par \plain\f0\fs12\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\b the -v switch\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 This switch tells \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\i CHInst\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  which version of Delphi the help file is to be registered with. Replace \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\i X\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  with the version of Delphi required - from 2 to \plain\f1\fs18\cf2 7\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 , e.g. -v5 for Delphi 5. If this switch is not provided then Delphi 4 is assumed.
\par \plain\f0\fs12\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\b the -q switch\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 This switch makes the program operate without generating any screen output. This is useful when calling \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\i CHInst\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  from batch files or installers where no screen output is required.
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect <BD 3>\plain\f1\fs8\cf2  \plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect </BD 3>\plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\i See also:\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
