{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\deff0\deftab720\deflang2057{\fonttbl{\f0\fswiss Arial;}{\f1\fnil \fcharset0 Courier New;}{\f2\fswiss \fcharset0 Arial;}}{\colortbl\red0\green0\blue0;\red0\green128\blue0;\red0\green0\blue0;\red0\green0\blue255;}\pard \plain \plain\f0\fs20\cf1 \protect <NS 1>\plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs24\cf3\b Uninstall Help Files Using The Command Line\plain\f0\fs20\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2  \plain\f0\fs20\cf1 \protect </NS 1>\plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 This topic describes how to uninstall help files using the \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\i CHInst\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  command line tool.
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\i CHInst\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  can uninstall (de-integrate) help files from \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\i Delphi\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 . It can optionally delete the help file and / or unregister it with Windows. The program can only be used to uninstall help files that were installed using version 2 or later of the GUI application or command line tool.
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 The command to issue unistall a previusly installed help file is:
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \pard \li400 \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect <KP 4>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 CHInst -u \plain\f1\fs18\cf2\i help_file\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  [-r] [-x] [-v\plain\f1\fs18\cf2\i X\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 ]\plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </KP 4>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par \pard \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 The switches and parameters are described below.
\par \plain\f0\fs12\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\b the -u switch\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 This switch is required for uninstallation. The following \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\i help_file\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  name specifies the path and file name of the file being uninstalled. The -u switch must be the first item on the command line.
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 The \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\i help_file\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  name can include a \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 5>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 file path macro\plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 5>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 .
\par \plain\f0\fs12\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\b the -r switch\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 Use this switch if the help file is to be unregistered with Windows (i.e. its entry is deleted from the registry).
\par \plain\f0\fs12\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\b the -x switch\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 This switch causes the help file to be physically deleted. Use with care.
\par \plain\f0\fs12\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\b the -v switch\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 This switch tells \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\i CHInst\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  which version of \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\i Delphi\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  the help file is to be uninstalled from. Replace \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\i X\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  with the version of \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\i Delphi\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  required - from 2 to \plain\f2\fs18\cf2 7\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 , e.g. -v5 for \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\i Delphi 5\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 . If this switch is not provided then \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\i Delphi 4\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  is assumed.
\par \plain\f0\fs12\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\b the -q switch\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 This switch makes the program operate without generating any screen output. This is useful when calling \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\i CHInst\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  from batch files or (un)installers where no screen output is required.
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs20\cf1 \protect <BD 2>\plain\f0\fs8\cf2  \plain\f0\fs20\cf1 \protect </BD 2>\plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\i See also:\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
