{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\deff0\deftab720\deflang2057{\fonttbl{\f0\fswiss Arial;}{\f1\fswiss \fcharset0 Arial;}{\f2\fnil \fcharset0 Courier New;}{\f3\fnil \fcharset2 WingDings;}}{\colortbl\red0\green0\blue0;\red0\green128\blue0;\red0\green0\blue0;\red0\green0\blue255;}\pard \plain \plain\f0\fs20\cf1 \protect <NS 1>\plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs24\cf3\b Command Line Application\plain\f1\fs24\cf3\b  Example\plain\f0\fs20\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2  \plain\f0\fs20\cf1 \protect </NS 1>\plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par 
\par \plain\f1\fs18\cf2 In this example we'll create a batch file to install the DelphiDabbler Version Information component's help file into a selected version of Delphi. (A copy of the component is available from the \plain\f1\fs18\cf3 DelphiDabbler website\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 ).
\par \plain\f1\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f1\fs18\cf2 We will pass the required version as a parameter to the batch file, along with a switch indicating whether to install or uninstall. We will also flag up any errors. The batch file assumes that the \plain\f1\fs18\cf2\i TPJVersionInfo\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  help file - \plain\f2\fs18\cf2 PJVersionInfo.hlp\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  has been copied to the system's TEMP folder which we find by accessing the %TEMP% environment variable from the batch file.
\par \plain\f1\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f1\fs18\cf2 Here's the batch file (the line numbers are for reference only and are not part of the file. Note that some lines below have had to be folded over to display all the required information - they should be entered all on one line. The batch file needs to be executed from the same folder as the CHInst program.
\par \plain\f1\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f2\fs18\cf1 \protect <KP 5>\plain\f2\fs18\cf2 01  @echo off
\par \plain\f2\fs18\cf3 02  \plain\f2\fs18\cf2 if "%1" == "" goto err1
\par \plain\f2\fs18\cf3 03  \plain\f2\fs18\cf2 if "%2" == "" goto err2
\par \plain\f2\fs18\cf3 04  \plain\f2\fs18\cf2 if "%1" == "install" goto install
\par \plain\f2\fs18\cf3 05  \plain\f2\fs18\cf2 if "%1" == "uninstall" goto uninstall
\par \plain\f2\fs18\cf3 06  \plain\f2\fs18\cf2 goto err1
\par \plain\f2\fs18\cf3 07  \plain\f2\fs18\cf2 :install
\par \plain\f2\fs18\cf3 08  \plain\f2\fs18\cf2 chinst -i "%TEMP%\\PJVersionInfo.hlp" -q -c 
\par     $(HELP)\\PJVI.hlp 
\par     -d "Delphi Dabbler Version Info Component" -v%2 
\par \plain\f2\fs18\cf3 09  \plain\f2\fs18\cf2 if ERRORLEVEL 1 goto errinst
\par \plain\f2\fs18\cf3 10  \plain\f2\fs18\cf2 echo File installed to Delphi %2
\par \plain\f2\fs18\cf3 11  \plain\f2\fs18\cf2 goto end
\par \plain\f2\fs18\cf3 12  \plain\f2\fs18\cf2 :uninstall
\par \plain\f2\fs18\cf3 13  \plain\f2\fs18\cf2 chinst -u $(HELP)\\PJVI.hlp -q -r -x -v%2
\par \plain\f2\fs18\cf3 14  \plain\f2\fs18\cf2 if ERRORLEVEL 1 goto errinst
\par \plain\f2\fs18\cf3 15  \plain\f2\fs18\cf2 echo File uninstalled from Delphi %2
\par \plain\f2\fs18\cf3 16  \plain\f2\fs18\cf2 goto end
\par \plain\f2\fs18\cf3 17  \plain\f2\fs18\cf2 :errinst
\par \plain\f2\fs18\cf3 18  \plain\f2\fs18\cf2 echo CHINST return error %ERRORLEVEL%
\par \plain\f2\fs18\cf3 19  \plain\f2\fs18\cf2 goto end
\par \plain\f2\fs18\cf3 20  \plain\f2\fs18\cf2 :err1
\par \plain\f2\fs18\cf3 21  \plain\f2\fs18\cf2 echo First parameter must be "install" or "uninstall"
\par \plain\f2\fs18\cf3 22  \plain\f2\fs18\cf2 goto end
\par \plain\f2\fs18\cf3 23  \plain\f2\fs18\cf2 :err2
\par \plain\f2\fs18\cf3 24  \plain\f2\fs18\cf2 echo 2nd parameter (Delphi version) required
\par \plain\f2\fs18\cf3 25  \plain\f2\fs18\cf2 :end\plain\f2\fs18\cf1 \protect </KP 5>\plain\f2\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f1\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f1\fs18\cf2 The batch file works as follows:
\par \plain\f1\fs8\cf2 
\par \pard \fi-400 \li400 \tx400 \plain\f3\fs18\cf2 \'A7\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 \tab Lines 01 to 07 simply check the parameters are OK. 
\par \plain\f1\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f3\fs18\cf2 \'A7\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 \tab In lines 08 to 11 we attempt to install the help file and trap any error results (CHI returns > 0 on error) or report OK and end. Note we use a \plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 6>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 path macro\plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 6>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  to install into the required \plain\f2\fs18\cf2 Help\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  folder. We also use the %TEMP% environment variable to find the location of the temporary folder that contains the help file.
\par \plain\f1\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f3\fs18\cf2 \'A7\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 \tab Lines 12 to 16 are where the uninstallation is performed and either success or error are reported. Note that we are both removing the help file's registry entry (-r) and deleting the file copy (-x) - so be careful not to use this script where a help file is installed in >1 version of Delphi. 
\par \plain\f1\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f3\fs18\cf2 \'A7\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 \tab Lines 17 to 19 are used to report any error codes returned from the program, while lines 20 to 24 report any problems with parameters.
\par \pard \plain\f0\fs8\cf2  \plain\f1\fs8\cf2 .\plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs20\cf1 \protect <BD 2>\plain\f0\fs8\cf2  \plain\f0\fs20\cf1 \protect </BD 2>\plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\i See also:\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \pard \fi-400 \li400 \tx400 \plain\f0\fs20\cf1 \protect <BU 3>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 \tab \plain\f1\fs18\cf2 Installing help files using the command line application
\par \plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect <BU 4>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 \tab Uninstalling help files using the command line application\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par }

