\par \plain\f0\fs24\cf3\b How CHI Works\plain\f0\fs20\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2  \plain\f0\fs20\cf1 \protect </NS 1>\plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\b Overview\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\i CHI\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  works quite simply by \plain\f1\fs18\cf2 updating \plain\f1\fs18\cf2\i Delphi\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  help \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 configuration file\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 s\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  \plain\f1\fs18\cf2 with \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 statements required to integrate the help file with the \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\i Delphi OpenHelp\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  system. \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\i Delphi's\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  help contents file is then modified \plain\f1\fs18\cf2 as necessary \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 to refer to the configuration file\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 s\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 . \plain\f1\fs18\cf2\i CHI\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  also maintains a small configuration file to record which help files it has installed. \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 The  registry is also updated to register the help file and its path with Windows.
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f1\fs18\cf2\b Please note\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  that, in order to ensure that \plain\f1\fs18\cf2\i Delphi\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  takes note of the changes made when installing and uninstalling, \plain\f1\fs18\cf2\i CHI\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  deletes any existing \plain\f2\fs18\cf2 .gid\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  and \plain\f2\fs18\cf2 .ftg\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  files in the \plain\f1\fs18\cf2\i Delphi\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  \plain\f2\fs18\cf2 Help\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  folder. Since \plain\f2\fs18\cf2 .ftg\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  files store any word indexes used by the \plain\f1\fs18\cf2\i Find\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  tab in \plain\f1\fs18\cf2\i WinHelp\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 , these indexes will need to be rebuilt after installing component help files.\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\b Installation Details\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f1\fs18\cf2\i CHI\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  updates the following \plain\f1\fs18\cf2\i Delphi\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  files, stored in the \plain\f2\fs18\cf2 Help\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  sub folder of the \plain\f1\fs18\cf2\i Delphi\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  installation. (where \plain\f1\fs18\cf2\i X\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  is the \plain\f1\fs18\cf2\i Delphi\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  version number):
\par \plain\f1\fs8\cf2 
\par \pard \tx2000 \tx3600 \plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect <BD 6>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 \tab \plain\f1\fs18\cf2\i Delphi 3..6\tab Delphi 7\plain\f1\fs18\cf1\i \protect </BD 6>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f1\fs8\cf2  \plain\f1\fs18\cf2 Help contents file\tab \plain\f2\fs18\cf2 delphi\plain\f2\fs18\cf2\i X\plain\f2\fs18\cf2 .cnt\tab d7.cnt
\par \plain\f1\fs18\cf2 OpenHelp link file\tab \plain\f2\fs18\cf2 delphi\plain\f2\fs18\cf2\i X\plain\f2\fs18\cf2 .ohi\tab d7.ohi
\par \plain\f1\fs18\cf2 OpenHelp index file\tab \plain\f2\fs18\cf2 delphi\plain\f2\fs18\cf2\i X\plain\f2\fs18\cf2 .ohl\tab d7.ohl
\par \plain\f1\fs18\cf2 CHI Config file\tab \plain\f2\fs18\cf2 CHId\plain\f2\fs18\cf2\i X\plain\f2\fs18\cf2 .cfg\tab CHId7.cfg
\par \pard \plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect <BD 5>\plain\f1\fs8\cf2  \plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect </BD 5>\plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f1\fs18\cf2 For Delphi 6 and 7 \plain\f1\fs18\cf2\i CHI\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  also updates the compiler's \plain\f2\fs18\cf2 .als\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  file. In Delphi 6 this is \plain\f2\fs18\cf2 delphi6.als\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  and in Delphi 7 it is \plain\f2\fs18\cf2 d7.als\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 . This is only done if there an .als file in the same folder as the help file and it has the same name.
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f1\fs18\cf2 The files are update as follows, asumming \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 we are installing a file named \plain\f3\fs18\cf2 MyHelpFile.hlp\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  into \plain\f3\fs18\cf2 C:\\MyHelpFolder\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  with a \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 description \plain\f1\fs18\cf2 of \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 "My Description"\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 :
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \pard \fi-400 \li400 \tx400 \plain\f4\fs18\cf2 \'A7\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 \tab \plain\f1\fs18\cf2 If it doesn't already exist the \plain\f1\fs18\cf2\i CHI\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  config file is created. \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\i Users should never edit this file manually.\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par \pard \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \pard \fi-400 \li400 \tx400 \plain\f4\fs18\cf2 \'A7\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 \tab The following entr\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 y is\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  added to \plain\f1\fs18\cf2 the \plain\f1\fs18\cf2\i CHI\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  config file:\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par \pard \fi-400 \li1200 \tx400 \plain\f3\fs18\cf2 :\plain\f5\fs18\cf2 Installed\plain\f3\fs18\cf2  MyHelpFile.hlp
\par \pard \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \pard \fi-400 \li400 \tx400 \plain\f4\fs18\cf2 \'A7\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 \tab \plain\f1\fs18\cf2 The Help contents file is updated to reference the \plain\f1\fs18\cf2\i OpenHelp\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  link and index files by ensuring the file contains the following lines:\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par \pard \fi-400 \li1200 \tx400 \plain\f6\fs18\cf2 :Include delphi4.ohi
\par :Include delphi4.ohl\plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \pard 
\par \pard \fi-400 \li400 \tx400 \plain\f4\fs18\cf2 \'A7\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 \tab \plain\f1\fs18\cf2 The following line is added to the \plain\f1\fs18\cf2\i OpenHelp\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  link file:
\par \pard \fi-400 \li1200 \tx400 \plain\f6\fs18\cf2 :\plain\f2\fs18\cf2 Link\plain\f6\fs18\cf2  \plain\f2\fs18\cf2 MyHelpFile\plain\f6\fs18\cf2 .\plain\f2\fs18\cf2 hlp\plain\f6\fs18\cf2 
\par \pard \fi-400 \li400 \tx400 \plain\f1\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f4\fs18\cf2 \'A7\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 \tab \plain\f1\fs18\cf2 The following line is added to the \plain\f1\fs18\cf2\i OpenHelp\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  index file:
\par \pard \fi-400 \li1200 \tx400 \plain\f6\fs18\cf2 :\plain\f2\fs18\cf2 Index My Description=MyHelpFile.hlp\plain\f6\fs18\cf2 
\par \pard \fi-400 \li400 \tx400 \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f4\fs18\cf2 \'A7\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 \tab A string value named \plain\f3\fs18\cf2 MyHelpFile.hlp\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  with value \plain\f3\fs18\cf2 C:\\MyHelpFolder \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 is added to the \plain\f3\fs18\cf2 HK\plain\f5\fs18\cf2 LM\plain\f3\fs18\cf2 \\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Help\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  registry key:
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f4\fs18\cf2 \'A7\plain\f7\fs18\cf2 \tab In Delphi 6 and 7 \plain\f2\fs18\cf2 .als\plain\f7\fs18\cf2  files are merged into to the main \plain\f2\fs18\cf2 .als\plain\f7\fs18\cf2  file.\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par \pard 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\b Uninstallation Details\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\i CHI\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  should only be used to uninstall files that is has installed\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  - i.e the files that are listed in the \plain\f1\fs18\cf2\i CHI\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  config file\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 . The\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 se\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  files \plain\f1\fs18\cf2 are \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 displayed on the Remove page of the Windows application. When a help file is uninstalled \plain\f1\fs18\cf2 the following actions take place:
\par \plain\f1\fs8\cf2 
\par \pard \fi-400 \li400 \tx400 \plain\f4\fs18\cf2 \'A7\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 \tab The relevant \plain\f2\fs18\cf2 :Index\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  entry is removed from the \plain\f1\fs18\cf2\i OpenHelp\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  index file
\par \plain\f4\fs18\cf2 \'A7\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 \tab The relevant \plain\f2\fs18\cf2 :Link\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  entry is removed from the \plain\f1\fs18\cf2\i OpenHelp\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  link file
\par \plain\f4\fs18\cf2 \'A7\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 \tab The file's \plain\f2\fs18\cf2 :Installed\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  entry is removed from the \plain\f1\fs18\cf2\i CHI\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  config file. The config file is not deleted when empty.
\par \plain\f4\fs18\cf2 \'A7\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 \tab If the \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 user has specified that the file should be un-registered with Windows then the \plain\f1\fs18\cf2 registry entry under \plain\f3\fs18\cf2 H\plain\f5\fs18\cf2 KLM\plain\f3\fs18\cf2 \\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Help\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  is also deleted.
\par \pard \tx400 \plain\f1\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f1\fs18\cf2 Note that the help contents file is \plain\f1\fs18\cf2\b not\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  updated - the \plain\f2\fs18\cf2 :Include\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  lines for the \plain\f1\fs18\cf2\i OpenHelp\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  index and link files may still be required by \plain\f1\fs18\cf2\i OpenHelp\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 . In Delphi 6 and 7 keywords are not removed from the master \plain\f2\fs18\cf2 .als\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  file is not updated - there is no way of knowing if the same keywords are used by other help files.\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par \pard \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \pard \fi-400 \li400 \tx400 \plain\f0\fs20\cf1 \protect <BD 2>\plain\f0\fs8\cf2  \plain\f0\fs20\cf1 \protect </BD 2>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par \pard \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\i See also:\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
