{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\deff0\deftab720\deflang2057{\fonttbl{\f0\fswiss Arial;}{\f1\fswiss \fcharset0 Arial;}{\f2\fnil \fcharset2 WingDings;}{\f3\fmodern Courier New;}{\f4\fnil \fcharset0 Courier New;}{\f5\fnil \fcharset0 Arial;}}{\colortbl\red0\green0\blue0;\red0\green128\blue0;\red0\green0\blue0;\red0\green0\blue255;}\pard \plain \plain\f0\fs20\cf1 \protect <NS 1>\plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs24\cf3\b File Path Macros\plain\f0\fs20\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2  \plain\f0\fs20\cf1 \protect </NS 1>\plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 To assist in accessing files in Delphi's folders (the usual location for help files is in the Help subfolder of a Delphi installation), the following macros can be included at the start of file names  These macros work with the Windows application\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  and \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 the \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\i CHInst\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  command line tool.
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \pard \fi-400 \li400 \tx400 \plain\f2\fs18\cf2 \'A7\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 \tab \plain\f3\fs18\cf2 $(ROOT)\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  - this macro is replaced by the path to the root folder of the Delphi installation.
\par \plain\f2\fs18\cf2 \'A7\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 \tab \plain\f3\fs18\cf2 $(HELP)\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  - this macro is replaced by the path to the help folder of the Delphi installation.
\par \pard \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 In both cases the installation accessed is the selected version of Delphi. How the version is determined depends on the tool being used:
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \pard \fi-400 \li400 \tx400 \plain\f2\fs18\cf2 \'A7\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 \tab \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\i Windows application:\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  the version of Delphi selected in the combo box.
\par \plain\f2\fs18\cf2 \'A7\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 \tab \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\i Command line tool:\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  the version of Delphi specified in the -v command line switch.
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \pard \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 To use file path macros in the GUI, simply enter them at the start of a path name in the relevant edit box. To use on the command line type the macro name at the start of  a file name.
\par \plain\f0\fs12\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\b Example using command line tool\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 To install a help file that has been unzipped into \plain\f4\fs18\cf2 C:\\Unzip\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  into Delphi \plain\f1\fs18\cf2 6\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 's help folder, using the command line tool use:
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \pard \li400 \plain\f5\fs18\cf1 \protect <KP 3>\plain\f4\fs18\cf2 CHInst -i C:\\Unzip\\MyHelp.hlp -c\plain\f5\fs18\cf1 \protect </KP 3>\plain\f5\fs18\cf2 
\par \pard \li800 \plain\f5\fs18\cf1 \protect <KP 4>\plain\f4\fs18\cf2 $(HELP)\\MyHelp.hlp -v6\plain\f5\fs18\cf1 \protect </KP 4>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect <KP 5>\plain\f4\fs18\cf2 -d "My Help Description"\plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </KP 5>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par \pard \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 ensuring the command is all entered on one line.
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 And, to uninstall the file use
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \pard \li400 \plain\f4\fs18\cf1 \protect <KP 6>\plain\f4\fs18\cf2 CHInst -u $(HELP)\\  MyHelp.hlp -r -x -v3\plain\f4\fs18\cf1 \protect </KP 6>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par \pard \plain\f0\fs12\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\b Example using Windows application\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 To perform the same installation as above, select the install page and:
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \pard \fi-400 \li400 \tx400 \plain\f2\fs18\cf2 \'A7\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 \tab Enter \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\i C:\\Unzip\\MyHelp.hlp\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  in the \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\i Help file\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  edit box\plain\f0\fs18\cf2\i .\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f2\fs18\cf2 \'A7\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 \tab Enter \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\i $(HELP)\\MyHelp.hlp\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  in the \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\i Copy to\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  edit box.
\par \plain\f2\fs18\cf2 \'A7\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 \tab Select \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\i 3\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  in the \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\i Delphi\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  combo box.
\par \plain\f2\fs18\cf2 \'A7\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 \tab Click the \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\i Install\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  button.
\par \pard \tx400 \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 Uninstallation is acheived by selecting the installed file from the combo box on the \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\i Remove\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  page and clicking the \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\i Remove\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  button.\plain\f0\fs18\cf2\i 
\par \pard \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs20\cf1 \protect <BD 2>\plain\f0\fs8\cf2  \plain\f0\fs20\cf1 \protect </BD 2>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par }

